# Security configuration items can be set here. This file should be kept
# encrypted at rest; when Mutt is executed, it will call gnupg to descrypt
# the file and keep settings in memory, preventing you from having to maintain
# passwords in a cleartext file. Encrypt this file to secure.pgp and delete
# the original.

# Account-specific IMAP Passwords
account-hook @example      'set imap_pass="hackme123"'
